1
00:00:00,950 --> 00:00:01,810
Hi everyone.

2
00:00:02,370 --> 00:00:06,750
In this video I'll tell how to make a pyrotechnic product for New Year holidays.

3
00:00:07,470 --> 00:00:10,510
Similar to those sold in retail.

4
00:00:11,190 --> 00:00:12,270
We'll be making rockets.

5
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:15,750
And for which we'll need three main ingredients.

6
00:00:16,310 --> 00:00:18,710
First of which is potassium nitrate.

7
00:00:19,570 --> 00:00:25,830
On sale can be bought as crushed white-colored crystals.

8
00:00:26,370 --> 00:00:29,690
Potassium nitrate can be bought in plant supply stores.

9
00:00:30,350 --> 00:00:31,330
For plant protection.

10
00:00:31,910 --> 00:00:37,270
Or in stores selling fertilizers.

11
00:00:37,950 --> 00:00:44,330
In this case a half-kilogram package was bought.

12
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,830
From Buyskie Fertilizers brand.

13
00:00:47,730 --> 00:00:53,090
Or can be bought in smaller 25-gram packaging.

14
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:57,530
Next main ingredient is sorbitol.

15
00:00:57,530 --> 00:01:05,590
Also is in form of soft white crystals.

16
00:01:05,750 --> 00:01:11,410
Sorbitol is a substance that replaces sugar for diabetics.

17
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:15,790
Bought in pharmacies.

18
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:21,650
Usually sold by weight in half-kilograms.

19
00:01:23,450 --> 00:01:28,310
Such quantity enough for many experiments.

20
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:32,970
Well, third ingredient is sulfur.

21
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:38,550
In nature occurs as bright yellow crystals.

22
00:01:39,150 --> 00:01:45,310
Buy as crushed yellow powder.

23
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:49,930
Sulfur is bought in pet stores.

24
00:01:49,930 --> 00:01:52,510
In veterinary stores.

25
00:01:53,570 --> 00:01:58,570
Sold as additive to feed for cattle or birds.

26
00:01:59,490 --> 00:02:01,910
In this case such packaging.

27
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:06,930
In description read so sulfur is pure without impurities.

28
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:11,990
Or in such packaging can find.

29
00:02:13,910 --> 00:02:19,390
Next, when these substances are bought.

30
00:02:20,510 --> 00:02:23,450
Look at degree of drying of substances.

31
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,030
Visually substances should be wet.

32
00:02:28,370 --> 00:02:33,590
If needed, these powders are additionally dried on radiator.

33
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:44,530
After drying of our three components possibly will need additional grinding of potassium nitrate and sulfur.

34
00:02:44,770 --> 00:02:53,870
If component was before with moisture impurity and moisture evaporated, lumps may form.

35
00:02:54,690 --> 00:03:02,810
Substance lumps we crush with wooden object until uniform powder forms.

36
00:03:03,890 --> 00:03:19,590
With sorbitol such actions don't need to be done because sorbitol in rocket fuel preparation will melt to fluid mass and remaining components will be added to it.

37
00:03:21,950 --> 00:03:27,090
After grinding of substances move to their weighing.

38
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:37,130
For this we'll need some household scales capable of weighing substances to tenths of gram.

39
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:47,910
In this case such scales capable of precisely weighing weight of objects up to 200 grams and showing to hundredths.

40
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:50,350
This quite suits us.

41
00:03:50,350 --> 00:04:04,330
With help of scales we measure out our components in ratio 60 grams potassium nitrate, 30 grams sorbitol and 10 grams sulfur.

42
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:21,330
Such amount of mixed substances later enough for us to fill two such rocket engines to full working state.

43
00:04:22,650 --> 00:04:30,430
Next move to responsible moment, this is making rocket engine body.

44
00:04:30,430 --> 00:04:39,550
On how you make it will depend flight characteristics of your future pyrotechnic product.

45
00:04:39,970 --> 00:05:01,450
For making body we'll need plastic mandrel from water pipe with outer diameter 20 mm, drill diameter 2.5 mm, some metal object with polished surface, in this case piece of old screwdriver 10 cm

46
00:05:01,450 --> 00:05:07,590
long.

47
00:05:09,570 --> 00:05:20,210
And under outer diameter of this metal pin drill is selected, in this case outer diameter 4 mm.

48
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:34,330
Material of body is A4 paper, for making one blank we'll need 8 sheets of paper.

49
00:05:34,990 --> 00:05:47,890
Done by winding paper onto plastic mandrel, align paper ends and make full rotation.

50
00:05:47,890 --> 00:06:00,390
After making full rotation, draw your attention that rotation is done without glue, otherwise it'll be very hard to extract guide mandrel.

51
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:19,330
After that we smear remaining surface of sheet with PVA glue fully using brush, prior under all this need to lay oilcloth or polyethylene so as not to smear with glue

52
00:06:19,330 --> 00:06:21,490
working table surface.

53
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:50,950
Wind paper, this way wind 8 layers, smear each layer with glue, after which we get paper tube, extract body of mandrel and from one end form star from paper.

54
00:06:52,310 --> 00:07:09,430
This way, when there are 8 layers, paper will be much thicker, but due to that it's impregnated with glue, it'll also be pliable, after which star rays are placed one on top of another in a circle and

55
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:10,270
compressed.

56
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:15,330
And after this, as you folded, this all wrapped with thread.

57
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:22,430
Same manipulation we do with opposite side, fold and wrap.

58
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:26,870
In result you'll get such blank.

59
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:40,430
When we wrapped with thread, all this smeared with PVA glue, good impregnate each side, and get blank.

60
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:47,810
Blank subsequently after drying cut with utility knife into two halves.

61
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:52,210
In result we see from one blank get two bodies.

62
00:07:53,650 --> 00:08:02,170
Drying of this body done on radiator or directly on heating boiler not less than 12 hours.

63
00:08:02,170 --> 00:08:11,190
After glue dries, whole blank acquires rigidity.

64
00:08:11,810 --> 00:08:19,750
If knock on it, sound like metal object knocking on bone.

65
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:25,330
Body acquires rigidity and strength.

66
00:08:25,970 --> 00:08:30,950
Now weigh body without rocket fuel.

67
00:08:33,570 --> 00:08:43,130
Body weight in this case is 16 grams.

68
00:08:54,290 --> 00:09:14,910
After blank was divided into two bodies, move to drilling hole for gas exit that'll raise our pyrotechnic product.

69
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:20,650
Into sky this hole is called nozzle.

70
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:40,930
For which we'll need drill that with help of thinner drill we drill hole strictly vertically in center, after which we widen it with drill equal to outer diameter of rod.

71
00:09:40,930 --> 00:09:45,610
Next prepare our body for fuel pouring.

72
00:09:45,830 --> 00:09:48,910
For this into drilled hole rod is inserted.

73
00:09:49,850 --> 00:09:52,730
Rod should enter tightly, not wobble.

74
00:09:54,390 --> 00:10:03,410
And see that after its insertion rod is in center of rocket engine body.

75
00:10:04,410 --> 00:10:15,570
Also can note that rod height made so for us about one and a half centimeters left to body edge of engine.

76
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:24,510
Rod height will determine for us level of fuel pouring in rocket engine.

77
00:10:25,210 --> 00:10:28,390
Next these one and a half centimeters will be sealed.

78
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:32,230
Move to fuel preparation.

79
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:38,970
Cooking better on electric stove, but when none, cook on minimum fire.

80
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:44,870
And with help of metal object, in this case using fire diffuser.

81
00:10:45,670 --> 00:11:01,470
First, nitrate poured into ceramic or metal container needs to be well heated for 4-5 minutes so whole container is hot and powder inside it.

82
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:07,130
If this isn't done, then later when adding nitrate fuel will quickly thicken.

83
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:10,810
Heat nitrate, then set aside.

84
00:11:11,950 --> 00:11:21,330
After use metal little cup, can metal glass, jar, whoever has what at hand.

85
00:11:22,270 --> 00:11:25,090
And pour into it pure sorbitol.

86
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:29,110
Sorbitol needs to be brought to melting.

87
00:11:30,110 --> 00:11:37,670
Set, now can add fire and bring sorbitol to melting.

88
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:44,710
After 5 minutes of heating turn off strong fire.

89
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:49,910
See sorbitol melted.

90
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:54,790
White mass forms.

91
00:11:56,950 --> 00:12:04,770
Further melting done with stirring until full dissolution of all particles.

92
00:12:08,810 --> 00:12:11,910
Liquid mass forms.

93
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:28,450
Now when all fully melted, move to pouring nitrate into sorbitol melt.

94
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:32,610
Nitrate previously heated for us.

95
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:48,210
Pour nitrate, distribute over surface evenly.

96
00:12:49,450 --> 00:12:58,050
And after some heating on slow fire, do mixing.

97
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:29,360
For those cooking first time, recommend keeping water container nearby so in case of ignition cooking fuel container can be quickly lowered into water.

98
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:41,380
White mass forms, like semolina, uniform.

99
00:13:51,350 --> 00:14:04,970
Mix well and only after uniform mass formed, add sulfur, because sulfur leads to fuel thickening.

100
00:14:05,150 --> 00:14:11,090
Add it to composition at very last case.

101
00:14:12,830 --> 00:14:16,970
Distribute sulfur and do mixing.

102
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:47,350
At that fire continues to burn at minimum and warms our container.

103
00:14:49,730 --> 00:14:56,350
Uniform homogeneous mass forms, like this, already yellow-colored.

104
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:58,670
That's it, fuel ready.

105
00:14:59,670 --> 00:15:12,490
After this can turn off fire completely and time comes to pour fuel into rocket engine.

106
00:15:13,410 --> 00:15:21,770
Look for convenient stand, rod is in center and move to pouring.

107
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:40,960
Fuel hot, so flows easily.

108
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:30,020
Engine fully filled.

109
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:51,020
Slightly tap on its walls and fuel evenly settles inside body.

110
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:12,790
During fuel cooling in rocket engine body some shrinkage of it happens.

111
00:17:13,610 --> 00:17:17,750
Here visible central metal rod that's there.

112
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:26,790
Now about 5 minutes at tapping on body fuel thickens.

113
00:17:26,910 --> 00:17:29,890
Visible rod still slightly mobile.

114
00:17:31,110 --> 00:17:42,050
Will need about 5-10 more minutes for fuel to acquire needed consistency and internal pin can be removed.

115
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:57,590
While fuel hardens in first body, periodically heat remaining amount on low fire and do its stirring so as not to let fuel thicken.

116
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:15,650
Visible has thicker mass, so it needs to be periodically reheated to then also pour into next prepared body.

117
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:40,960
Fuel temperature need to keep so sulfur doesn't go into molten state.

118
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:46,680
That is, it should stay in form of fine dispersion of powder in fuel composition.

119
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,300
This important for its characteristic.

120
00:18:50,780 --> 00:18:59,860
And also in this fuel composition for more colorful effects can introduce powders of various metals.

121
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:08,740
For example, if introduce several grams of magnesium in composition, there'll be silver-white tail behind rocket.

122
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:13,640
Same color can add aluminum, copper will add greenish color.

123
00:19:14,060 --> 00:19:23,340
That is, with this can experiment and each will find interesting effect.

124
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:35,180
We heated fuel to initial state, now it can also be poured into body of second engine.

125
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:44,960
Composition quite thickened, now can move to removing rod from body.

126
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:51,960
Pull out carefully, rod will exit with tension.

127
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:02,820
For this it should be polished.

128
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:16,620
Did extraction and we have channel formed in center.

129
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:21,220
Example of how such fuel burns in open air.

130
00:20:45,670 --> 00:21:04,470
Rocket fuel by data given at start of video with sulfur addition has one distinctive feature from rocket fuel that doesn't have sulfur added.

131
00:21:05,970 --> 00:21:20,470
Ordinary rocket fuel where 60 grams potassium nitrate and 40 grams sorbitol are cooked, it hardens long, about day needed for hardening.

132
00:21:21,770 --> 00:21:30,450
Plus has not such mechanical properties as fuel with sulfur added.

133
00:21:30,450 --> 00:21:41,210
Sulfur also participates in rocket fuel burning with formation of bigger gas amount.

134
00:21:41,450 --> 00:21:46,590
And sulfur very well strengthens the fuel itself.

135
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:51,150
It transforms into structure resembling stone.

136
00:21:52,210 --> 00:22:06,870
Audible if knock with metal object, and quite strongly fuel doesn't crack, no cracks form, that is good mechanical properties.

137
00:22:07,290 --> 00:22:23,330
This very important so in body where fuel poured there are no voids, because voids or fuel cracking during engine operation can lead to anomalous burning and

138
00:22:23,330 --> 00:22:27,290
body rupture.

139
00:22:28,010 --> 00:22:33,050
We don't need this so we follow manufacturing technology.

140
00:22:34,050 --> 00:22:42,470
Fuel with sulfur added hardens in 10 hours to this state.

141
00:22:42,470 --> 00:22:49,730
After 10 hours this engine ready for use.

142
00:22:51,490 --> 00:22:55,710
Can install it on pyrotechnic product.

143
00:22:55,790 --> 00:23:02,970
In manufacturing process question may arise, why central channel is formed in rocket engine fuel.

144
00:23:02,970 --> 00:23:07,030
Now analyze this on example of this drawing.

145
00:23:07,570 --> 00:23:10,190
Schematically shown engine in cross-section.

146
00:23:10,410 --> 00:23:16,890
These are paper walls, paper cork and visible fuel with central channel.

147
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,710
Analyze burning process.

148
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:24,970
When igniting fuel it burns along whole length of central channel.

149
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:36,890
During burning central channel diameter constantly grows and fuel burns toward walls, and gas escapes through nozzle.

150
00:23:37,350 --> 00:23:48,930
This way we provide big diameter of burning fuel surface, fast its burning and as result formation of big pressure of exhaust gases.

151
00:23:49,410 --> 00:23:54,790
This way our pyrotechnic product gains very big speed.

152
00:23:54,970 --> 00:24:06,350
And able to rise to much greater height compared to engine that's filled with fuel without central channel.

153
00:24:07,790 --> 00:24:26,630
Second plus of such design is that burning fuel in central channel protects engine body walls from burning temperature and also protects it from pressure of exhaust

154
00:24:26,630 --> 00:24:27,110
gases.

155
00:24:27,650 --> 00:24:33,150
So main working zone for us is rocket engine nozzle.

156
00:24:33,150 --> 00:24:41,520
So to rocket engine nozzle big requirements in plan of manufacturing.

157
00:24:42,010 --> 00:24:45,610
It should be very well glued and wrapped with thread.

158
00:24:45,850 --> 00:24:49,410
This is main part of rocket engine.

159
00:24:49,890 --> 00:24:54,270
Now I'll show engine that's properly worked.

160
00:24:55,530 --> 00:24:59,430
Managed to find our model.

161
00:25:00,430 --> 00:25:02,930
See that it was in operation.

162
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:07,810
And can pay attention to nozzle.

163
00:25:08,130 --> 00:25:15,590
Visible that form didn't change, nozzle isn't torn, thread remained intact.

164
00:25:16,270 --> 00:25:21,570
Small burning zone during operation.

165
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:31,810
Walls also remained strong, they don't push through from hand force.

166
00:25:32,570 --> 00:25:38,670
That is, engine worked stably without destruction of integrity of its construction.

167
00:25:40,930 --> 00:25:50,190
Now I'll show example of engine that was in operation but in it central channel didn't form.

168
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:57,890
This engine to this point was filled with fuel.

169
00:25:58,370 --> 00:26:01,650
And can pay attention to what happened to nozzle.

170
00:26:02,270 --> 00:26:06,630
Thread burned, there are burns in several places.

171
00:26:09,330 --> 00:26:13,670
And the nozzle itself is torn from pressing gases.

172
00:26:14,330 --> 00:26:24,990
Can observe that tube easily crumples, which means walls strongly thinned during rocket fuel burning.

173
00:26:26,750 --> 00:26:40,010
After this demonstration I'll show video of how launch of this pyrotechnic product was done and what it led to.

174
00:26:43,830 --> 00:26:48,080
Move to forming rocket engine cork.

175
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:57,130
This part has special requirements since on it very big pressure from exhaust gases is exerted.

176
00:26:58,070 --> 00:27:12,310
And pressure is of such force that if your cork is poorly made, it'll just knock it out and rocket either won't fly at all or fly to insignificant height.

177
00:27:12,310 --> 00:27:20,130
Part is very responsible, so it needs to be well fixed to body.

178
00:27:20,630 --> 00:27:40,730
For cork to glue well to body, need to remove first layer of paper that wasn't impregnated with glue when we rolled body on mandrel of plastic tube.

179
00:27:41,730 --> 00:27:51,550
This layer of paper is removed and bent over surface of fuel itself.

180
00:27:52,410 --> 00:28:01,890
This layer will protect channel in rocket engine fuel from glue getting in.

181
00:28:02,620 --> 00:28:18,400
This way it's scraped off and lowered on fuel surface to layer that's quality glued.

182
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:31,250
This needs to be done, otherwise this paper that holds badly may just be torn off by gas pressure.

183
00:28:31,890 --> 00:28:35,150
Together I'll show with cork.

184
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:42,890
Small video where clearly visible the moment when cork is poorly made.

185
00:28:55,450 --> 00:29:06,750
Paper well pressed and hole made to depth about 3 mm, after which into hole fuse is placed.

186
00:29:06,750 --> 00:29:22,210
This way we form fuse ignition time at the moment when fuel burned to greater degree and burning reached directly walls.

187
00:29:22,710 --> 00:29:25,570
After which fuse ignition happens.

188
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:35,250
It burns for one and a half seconds, passing through cork, after which ignition of ejection charge happens.

189
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:45,990
For forming cork body we'll need porous fabric, medical bandage works well and water-based glue.

190
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:57,530
For starts, well smear with glue walls and surface of rocket engine fuel.

191
00:29:57,530 --> 00:30:00,150
For

192
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:09,060
this use wooden stick.

193
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:52,960
Need to smear whole surface and very well so bandage impregnates and quality glues.

194
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:55,640
Bandage

195
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:20,440
cut into strips about 10 cm and immerse into body.

196
00:31:50,700 --> 00:32:01,980
Next material should be well compacted, at that the fuse itself needs to be pressed to body wall.

197
00:32:26,620 --> 00:32:32,280
Then impregnation of first layer happens over surface.

198
00:32:56,290 --> 00:33:05,150
Impregnate very well so whole fabric filled with glue.

199
00:33:07,050 --> 00:33:15,430
This provides quality adhesion and gluing of surface to rocket engine body.

200
00:33:54,250 --> 00:33:58,630
Fuse for igniting should be taken thicker.

201
00:33:58,770 --> 00:34:07,750
If fuse from pyrotechnic products is thin, then better lay it 2-3 pieces in one bundle.

202
00:34:11,410 --> 00:34:14,850
First layer well impregnated.

203
00:34:15,790 --> 00:34:17,510
Introduce second bandage layer.

204
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:57,660
After introducing second layer do interesting operation.

205
00:34:59,700 --> 00:35:05,000
Start forming sewing with help of wire or thread.

206
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:14,540
For this at depth of second layer surface hole made with help of awl.

207
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:29,200
Next circle outlined along which sewing height will go.

208
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:42,060
Along contour hole made approximately every 8 mm.

209
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:38,780
Next move to sewing with help of wire.

210
00:36:39,780 --> 00:36:50,040
Wire is pulled through hole and laid with intersection in center.

211
00:36:50,420 --> 00:36:59,520
With transition to one hole and transferred to next opposite.

212
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:08,900
This way we form mesh that tightly presses first two layers of fabric to fuel.

213
00:37:09,180 --> 00:37:14,580
After glue hardening quality plug will form.

214
00:37:15,300 --> 00:37:26,120
Next we'll lay subsequent layer of glue-impregnated material and last layer with paper plug.

215
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:31,640
After sewing such wire surface forms.

216
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:37,840
More convenient even to sew with help of thread and needle in these holes, comes out faster.

217
00:37:37,940 --> 00:37:42,560
Took wire for clarity, so it's visible how formed.

218
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:48,260
Next once more impregnate surface with glue.

219
00:37:55,040 --> 00:38:09,720
This quality gluing has decisive significance so your cork isn't knocked out during operation, or burns through.

220
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:49,260
Also one more layer of bandage is added, after which already glued with porous paper.

221
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,220
Can take napkin.

222
00:38:52,100 --> 00:39:05,060
Last hole closed and flat surface formed equal in height to engine body.

223
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:17,580
Before paper laying layer fully poured with glue and its full impregnation happens.

224
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:23,420
Then on this glue paper lays.

225
00:39:29,600 --> 00:39:40,160
For strength can add fine sawdust here, or add gypsum.

226
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:52,900
Mix with glue, will increase strength and reduce drying time of glue itself.

227
00:39:54,760 --> 00:40:03,740
In practice can experiment and find most optimal constructions for own solutions.

228
00:40:04,690 --> 00:40:16,260
After plug fully dried, move to forming part that's responsible for light-noise effects in sky.

229
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:21,420
For this need to make tubes from paper of various diameters.

230
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:26,540
Can much bigger diameter than rocket engine itself.

231
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,800
All depends what you want to fill it with.

232
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:34,060
In this case I took body offcut.

233
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:36,380
Now we fix it.

234
00:40:36,740 --> 00:40:44,280
Visible that fuse comes out for igniting working substance.

235
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:49,580
Fix it on body with help of adhesive tape.

236
00:41:17,760 --> 00:41:21,140
What can be used as filling?

237
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:25,440
As filling can use absolutely anything.

238
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:33,240
Any cheap pyrotechnic products that can burn with help of sparkling stars.

239
00:41:35,620 --> 00:41:43,060
Can use such balls with sparkling stars, filling from them.

240
00:41:43,060 --> 00:41:48,320
Can load some quantity of firecrackers here.

241
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:56,940
If you have larger diameter tube, then quantity of firecrackers will fit much more.

242
00:41:57,780 --> 00:42:03,360
This, I repeat, for example took model, what can be done.

243
00:42:04,980 --> 00:42:10,980
Now, what does filling serve as ejection charge for such construction?

244
00:42:11,900 --> 00:42:16,700
I, say, use black powder of homemade production.

245
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:23,380
But can also use filling from pyrotechnic products.

246
00:42:23,940 --> 00:42:29,980
Can use as ejection charge granules from same rocket fuel.

247
00:42:29,980 --> 00:42:35,940
Granules are rolled into small balls 3-4 mm diameter and fill about 1 cm.

248
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:45,500
In this case I fill working zone with black powder.

249
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:58,880
For reliable ejection charge operation about 1 cm enough.

250
00:43:03,780 --> 00:43:10,100
And for spectacle and effect add metal powders.

251
00:43:11,040 --> 00:43:18,440
In this case I'll add some quantity of magnesium powder.

252
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:20,920
Now

253
00:43:32,850 --> 00:43:37,010
composition should be slightly mixed.

254
00:43:43,240 --> 00:43:58,060
Magnesium will give in sky beautiful flash of silver-white color, that'll be visible, observing

255
00:44:01,150 --> 00:44:01,810
mixture.

256
00:44:01,810 --> 00:44:12,990
Now can move to installation of components that'll be ejected by gas pressure and work in air.

257
00:44:13,050 --> 00:44:17,850
In this case will use firecrackers.

258
00:44:25,390 --> 00:44:29,410
Then charge with sparkling stars.

259
00:44:29,790 --> 00:44:37,610
Whole filling should freely come out from ejection charge pressure.

260
00:44:39,330 --> 00:44:42,310
It descends without special effort.

261
00:44:42,630 --> 00:44:48,630
Also use sparkling stars from pyrotechnic product.

262
00:44:49,850 --> 00:44:54,690
Plastic balls that rupture with crack.

263
00:44:54,970 --> 00:44:56,690
Take their filling.

264
00:44:58,690 --> 00:45:07,430
Add some powder for reliable igniting of this part of filling.

265
00:45:08,430 --> 00:45:16,010
Fuse tip I lower into this zone.

266
00:45:17,290 --> 00:45:25,130
As nose cone we'll be served by part from disassembled ball.

267
00:45:25,390 --> 00:45:27,290
It very well sits here.

268
00:45:28,290 --> 00:45:30,410
Like this.

269
00:45:31,450 --> 00:45:36,810
Becomes like little cap and holds very tightly.

270
00:45:38,410 --> 00:45:41,190
Our demonstration product ready.

271
00:45:42,750 --> 00:45:50,070
Now I'll fix it with help of adhesive tape on wooden stabilizer.

272
00:45:50,070 --> 00:45:54,130
Wooden stabilizer length about 80 cm.

273
00:45:55,950 --> 00:45:59,280
And we'll test its flight characteristics.

274
00:46:00,270 --> 00:46:01,670
Product in ready form.

275
00:46:03,150 --> 00:46:07,810
Attached to wooden stabilizer with help of adhesive tape.

276
00:46:08,810 --> 00:46:21,290
Visible that need to combine rocket engine channel center with wooden guide.

277
00:46:21,830 --> 00:46:37,790
And as fuse for igniting rocket fuel will use two factory little fuses twisted with thread from cheap pyrotechnic products.

278
00:46:39,350 --> 00:46:47,730
Fuse, so it's reliably fixed, bent and introduced into engine.

279
00:46:54,080 --> 00:46:57,540
Now weigh our ready product.

280
00:47:09,990 --> 00:47:12,660
Weight is 96 grams.
